test-rating.description: GreatSchools Ratings for Washington are based on the 2012-2013 Measurements of Student Progress (MSP), End-of-Course (EOC), and High School Proficiency Exam (HSPE) reading, writing, math and science results. GreatSchools compared the test results for each grade and subject across all Washington schools and divided them into 1 through 10 ratings (10 is the best). Please note, private schools are not required to release test results, so ratings are available only for public schools. GreatSchools Ratings cannot be compared across states, because of differences in the states' standardized testing programs. Keep in mind that when comparing schools using GreatSchools Ratings it's important to factor in other information, including the quality of each school's teachers, the school culture, special programs, etc.
